Title : Kilbella River
Text : The '''Kilbella River''' is a [[river]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], flowing into Kilbella Bay, which is an arm of [[Rivers Inlet]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/3835.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kilbella River"]</ref>

The [[Chuckwalla River]] also flows into [[Kilbella Bay]] via the same valley.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/26769.html BC Names/GeobC entry "Chuckwalla River"]</ref> The Kilbella River is considered to be a stream and is nearby Kiltala Indian Reserve 2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mapcarta.com/24329286|title=Kilbella River|website=Mapcarta|language=en|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref> <!--with a different estuary maybe? Hard to say from the map; I'll consult BC Names, maybe there's an error here-->

